# make a copy 
rgb_img = img.copy()

# convert to grayscale 
gray_img = img.convert('L')
gray_img2 = gray_img.copy()

for i in range (0,img.size[0]):
    for j in range (0,img.size[1]):
        r, g, b = rgb_img.getpixel((i, j))
        gray_img2.putpixel((i,j), (gray_img2.getpixel((i, j))*(i%50))//50)
        if(g > r+b):
            rgb_img.putpixel((i,j), (0,0,0))
        

#setting figure size 
plt.figure(figsize=(20,20))

#plotting the four images 
plt.subplot(2,2,1)
plt.imshow(img)

plt.subplot(2,2,2)
plt.imshow(gray_img, cmap="gray")

plt.subplot(2,2,3)
plt.imshow(rgb_img)

plt.subplot(2,2,4)
plt.imshow(gray_img2, cmap="gray")
